FBIS4-40708 "drsov118_f_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 National Affairs Attempt Made on Life of People's Deputy Candidate Attempt Made on Life of People's Deputy Candidate LD1806142894 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 17 Jun 94 LD1806142894 Kiev UNIAN Ukrainian BFN [Text] Kharkov, [no date as received] -- As a UNIAN correspondent learned, on 16 June an attempt was made on the life of Oleksiy Stelmakh, age 28, a people's deputy candidate of the city council, Constituency No. 70, and editor of the independent city newspaper V KAZHDYY DOM [TO EVERY HOUSE] with the largest circulation in the city. A stranger accosted him at the entrance to the editorial office and hit him several times on the head with a heavy metal object, thus inflicting grave bodily injuries. The stranger disappeared. In an interview with a UNIAN correspondent Oleksiy Stelmakh said he believed this was a political attempt, because his chances of winning in the constituency were extremely high. Criminal proceedings have been instituted in connection with this attack.
